---
title: "bridgeAssets (FeeAggregator)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_check_access: require whenNotPaused, BRIDGER_ROLE
    q_check_access --> q_check_receiver: access granted
    q_check_receiver --> q_revert_receiver: NOT s_allowlistedReceivers[chain].contains(bridgeReceiver)
    q_revert_receiver --> [*]: revert ReceiverNotAllowlisted
    q_check_receiver --> q_check_empty: receiver allowlisted
    q_check_empty --> q_revert_empty: bridgeAssetAmounts.length == 0
    q_revert_empty --> [*]: revert EmptyList
    q_check_empty --> q_build_msg: not empty
    q_build_msg --> q_get_fee: build CCIP message with allowlisted assets
    q_get_fee --> q_check_balance: fees = ccipRouter.getFee()
    q_check_balance --> q_revert_insufficient: fees > linkBalance
    q_revert_insufficient --> [*]: revert InsufficientBalance
    q_check_balance --> q_approve_link: sufficient balance
    q_approve_link --> q_send: safeIncreaseAllowance(ccipRouter, fees)
    q_send --> [*]: ccipRouter.ccipSend(destinationChain, message)

    note right of q_build_msg
        INV-001: Only allowlisted assets can be bridged
        INV-002: Only allowlisted receivers on allowlisted chains can receive
        INV-003: LINK token used for fee payment
        INV-004: Each bridged asset approved to CCIP router individually
    end note
